      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "Πάντα",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "all things",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") even the state of men’s hearts. Even though thou art asked no question by any man, yet thy words are adapted to all.—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "καὶ οὐ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "and",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " thou needest ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "not",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") There is one Teacher alone, who, without being asked, satisfies the wants of His disciples. Many in our days learn but little, because they are not wont to ask any questions of their teachers, who certainly are not omniscient [so as to know their wants without being told them].—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "πιστεύομεν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ὅτι ἀπὸ Θεοῦ ἐξῆλθες",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "we believe that Thou earnest forth from God",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "i.e.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " we “believe in God, and believe also in Thee.” And so Jesus has convinced them. Comp. ch. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 14:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Believe",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Imperative",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", not Indic. as Engl. Vers. See Beng., note).",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
